cs.CL, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper involves natural language processing and robotics, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper focuses on generating natural language instructions. The second most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics) since the paper involves developing a navigational guide model for robots. The third most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper involves machine learning techniques such as inverse reinforcement learning and neural machine translation. The fourth most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper involves developing a machine learning model for generating natural language instructions. The fifth most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) since the paper involves conducting navigation experiments with human participants.
